  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Peel and slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong> into rings</p><p>Slice your <strong>cucumber</strong> finely into discs</p><p>Add the <strong>cucumber discs</strong> and<strong> cider vinegar</strong> to a bowl with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>sugar</strong> and set aside – these are your<strong> 'pickles'</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1707841970727-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1707841970727-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1707841970727-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1707841970727-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1707841970727-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Put a large baking tray (or two) in the oven to heat up (this will stop the pizza bottoms from going soggy!)</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>beef mince</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Once browned, set aside until you're ready to build your pizza</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1707841973608-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1707841973608-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1707841973608-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1707841973608-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1707841973608-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add a handful of <strong>flour </strong>to a plate and a splash of <strong>milk </strong>to a shallow bowl</p><p>Add your <strong>panko breadcrumbs </strong>and<strong> ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) to a separate plate with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and mix it all together</p><p>Season your <strong>chicken breast strips</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, coat them in <strong>flour</strong>, tap off any excess, then add them to the <strong>milk </strong>and finally press them into the <strong>breadcrumbs </strong>firmly to coat evenly – these are your <strong>breaded chicken dippers</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1707841976640-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1707841976640-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1707841976640-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1707841976640-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1707841976640-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>breaded chicken dippers </strong>to a baking tray (or two!) and put the tray[s] in the oven for<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>18-20 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) – these are your <strong>chicken dippers</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1707841981110-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1707841981110-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1707841981110-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1707841981110-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1707841981110-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>tomato paste</strong> to a bowl with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and<strong> </strong>4 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[6 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[8 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>tomato sauce</strong></p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1707841983585-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1707841983585-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1707841983585-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1707841983585-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1707841983585-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove the heated tray[s] from the oven and add your <strong>pizza base[s]</strong></p><p>Spread the <strong>tomato sauce</strong> evenly all over the <strong>pizza base[s] </strong>with the back of a spoon</p><p>Top with the<strong> browned mince</strong> and <strong>grated cheddar</strong> and place the tray[s] in the oven for 12-15 min or or until the cheese has melted, the base is crisp and the beef is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>'cheeseburger' pizza</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1707841987191-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1707841987191-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1707841987191-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1707841987191-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1707841987191-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the pizza is cooking, combine your <strong>mustard ketchup </strong>and <strong>tomato ketchup</strong> in a bowl with 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>burger sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1707841989984-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1707841989984-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1707841989984-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1707841989984-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1707841989984-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> 'cheeseburger' pizza</strong> with the <strong>chicken dippers </strong>to the side</p><p>Top the pizza with <strong>half</strong> the <strong>'pickles' </strong>and the <strong>shallot rings</strong></p><p>Drizzle most of the <strong>burger sauce </strong>over the<strong> </strong>top<strong> </strong>and serve any<strong> remaining</strong> '<strong>pickles' </strong>and <strong>burger sauce </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
